				},
				"description": {
					"value": "<p><strong>Trigger</strong> Foleghant use the Shield Block reaction, and the opponent that triggered Shield Block is adjacent to him and is up to two size larger than him or less</p><hr /><p>Foleghant pushes back as he blocks the attack, knocking his foe away or off balance. Foleghant uses his shield to push the triggering creature, either automatically Shoving it 5 feet or causing it to become flat-footed until the start of your next turn. The triggering creature chooses whether to be moved or become @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.AJh5ex99aV6VTggg]{Off-Guard}. If it chooses to be moved, he chooses the direction. If the Shove would cause it to hit a solid object, enter a square of difficult terrain, or enter another creature's space, it must become @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.AJh5ex99aV6VTggg]{Off-Guard} instead of being moved. When a creature Foleghant Shove has to stop moving because it would hit an object, it takes 6 bludgeoning damage. This happens regardless of how Foleghant Shoved the creature.</p>",
